<paragraph id="A7670207FFDCFFBC60AC168151C2E78D" blockId="1.[151,1437,400,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<keyLead id="1C29A132FFDCFFBC60AC168151C2E78D" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
1. Antenniferous tubercles armed with short spiny projection; humeri with one stout conical protuberance; calli with deep hole, behind posterior third; anterolateral margins of pronotum with one conical protuberance; posterior half of connexival segments III–VI conspicuously swollen; hemelytral membrane absent; postocular tubercle hemispheric, faintly insinuate over the surface (
<figureCitation id="3FE31E82FFDCFFBC60D216F95573E78E" box="[233,300,488,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1676,1700]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,429,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-114@2.[151,1436,417,1653]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Dorsal view of Monasavuhygia spp. 1, M. cordata Brailovsky, 1996 (female). 2, M. fodina sp. nov. (female). 3, M. incola sp. nov. (female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5851261/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="3FE31E82FFDCFFBC610C16F9551AE78D" box="[311,325,488,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1432,1456]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,322,1395]" captionTargetId="figure-67@3.[151,1436,309,1409]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–6. Female genital plates in caudal view of Monasavuhygia spp. 4, M. cordata Brailovsky, 1996. 5, M. fodina sp. nov. 6, M. incola sp. nov. FIGURES 7–9. Female genital plates in lateral view of Monasavuhygia spp. 7, M. cordata Brailovsky, 1996. 8, M. fodina sp. nov. 9, M. incola sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5851263/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">6</figureCitation>
, 9)........................................................... 
<emphasis id="95ACDE15FFDCFFBC640F16F950BAE78E" bold="true" box="[1076,1253,487,509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<taxonomicName id="60D87984FFDCFFBC640F16F950CCE78E" authority="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera, 2022" authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2022" box="[1076,1171,487,509]" class="Insecta" family="Coreidae" genus="Monasavuhygia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incola" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="95ACDE15FFDCFFBC640F16F950CCE78E" bold="true" box="[1076,1171,487,509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">M. incola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8E9F636EFFDCFFBC64A216F950BAE78E" box="[1177,1253,488,509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry id="DFCF4297FFDCFFBC64C916F951CAE78D" box="[1266,1429,488,510]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7670207FFDCFFBC60AC151451C3E426" blockId="1.[151,1437,400,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<keyLead id="1C29A132FFDCFFBC60AC151451C3E426" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">- Antenniferous tubercles unarmed; humeri unarmed; calli lacking a hole behind posterior third; anterolateral margins of pronotum without conical protuberance; posterior half of connexival segments III–VI conspicuously swollen or not; hemelytral membrane absent or present; postocular tubercle slightly protuberant or lacking.................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
